@node Installation
@chapter Installation

Nael's LSP-based features (via Eglot or lsp-mode), require Lean version 4 to be @uref{https://lean-lang.org/install/manual/, installed}.  If you want to use lsp-mode, you might need to install lsp-mode before @code{nael-lsp}.

@menu
* Installation from Melpa::
* Installation from Sources::
@end menu

@node Installation from Melpa
@section Installation from Melpa

@code{nael} is available on @uref{https://melpa.org/#/nael, Melpa} (and @uref{https://stable.melpa.org/#/nael, Melpa-Stable}) but @code{nael-lsp} not yet.  To install, first add the package-archive by adding this code to your Emacs initialization file and evaluating it interactively.

@lisp
(require 'package)
(add-to-list 'package-archives '("melpa" . "https://melpa.org/packages/") t)
(package-initialize)
@end lisp

Then type @samp{M-x package-refresh-contents RET}.  Finally, choose one of the following approaches:  To install interactively, type @samp{M-x package-install RET nael RET}.  To install via package selection, add @samp{(setopt package-selected-packages '(nael))} to your init file, evaluate it, and type @samp{M-x package-install-selected-packages RET}.  To install via Use-Package, add @samp{(use-package nael :ensure t)} to your init file and evaluate it.

